irrelevant money-growth indicator in analysis and communication,
but will keep secret the inflation forecast that will, in practice,
be the decisive input in policy decisions. Exchange rate policy is
controlled by the Council of finance ministers in the EMU; this is
a major inconsistency in the Maastricht Treaty and a possible threat
