have a crucial role in ensuring the accountability of the Eurosystem;
the minimum transparency needed for effective outside monitoring
and evaluation of the Eurosystem's policy decisions seem to require
published inflation forecasts and, most likely, published minutes
and voting records of the Governing Council.},
