whatever the ostensible exchange-rate regime. Fiscal tightening and
more exchange-rate flexibility offer a sounder eventual response.
Poor incentives and corporate governance in banks should have been
anticipated: subsequent improvements were slow and costly. Large
investments in writing off bad debt and providing adequate resources
