determinants of the exchange rate (the terms of trade, relative price
on nontraded to traded goods, the stock of net foreign assets, and
a proxy for the risk premium) and another that involves the short-run
effect of the interest rate differential. The estimated BEERs, including
those generated with calibrated values of the explanatory variables
using the Hodrick-Prescott filter, are used to shed light on the
consistency of the three exchange rates with economic fundamentals,
and are also compared with FEERs estimated by Williamson (1994).},
author = {Clark, Peter B and MacDonald, Ronald},
journal = {International Monetary Fund Working Paper},
number = {67},
title = {{Exchange Rates and Economic Fundamentals - A Methodological Comparison of BEERs and FEERs}},
