particularly in inflation expectations and in monetary policy frameworks,
that should help in containing inflation and lowering the costs of
doing so. However, except in the United States and the United Kingdom,
there is little evidence yet of fundamental changes in wage and price
behaviour underlying the flexibility of labour and product markets;
