on whether they have access to public bond markets as measured by
the firm having a debt rating. Although firms with a debt rating
are fundamentally different, these differences do not explain our
findings. Even after controlling for the firm characteristics previously
found to determine observed capital structure and the possible endogeneity
of having a bond rating, we find that firms which are able to raise
debt from public markets have 40 percent more debt.},
